        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 8:30PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 830 PM CDT/730 PM MDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm near Trail City, or 15 miles southwest of Mobridge,
moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mobridge, Timber Lake, Little Eagle, Wakpala, White Horse, Firesteel,
New Everets Resort, Little Moreau Rec Area, Trail City, Indian Creek
Rec Area, Blackfoot, Spring Lake, Indian Memorial Rec Area, Promise,
Swan Creek Rec Area, Revheim Bay Rec Area, Grand River Casino, Klein
Ranch, Glencross, and southeastern Standing Rock Nation.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT/900
PM MDT/ for north central South Dakota.</instruction>
